- Added supply-chain integrity checks to the Fleet-maintained apps pipeline: a new verification tool (`cmd/maintained-apps/verify`) downloads changed installers and independently verifies their SHA256 against the manifest before the automated update PR opens, publisher signing identities can be pinned per app (Apple Developer ID Team ID with notarization on macOS, Authenticode subject CN on Windows) and are verified at ingest and again in the validator before install scripts run, and the validator now scans Windows installers with Microsoft Defender. All checks currently run in report-only mode.
